{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6d9ba2ea-f5f0-4926-8dd4-9a457c01e2fd","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Target Framework Problems:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ Not supported by MSTest v3. It requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET Core targets.\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ Also not supported. .NET 5 is out of support and dropped by MSTest v3.\n- **`net462`** — ✅ Still supported (.NET Framework 4.6.2 is the minimum).\n\n**Package Changes:**\nMSTest v3 consolidates into a single `MSTest` package, replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to:\n1. Update your target frameworks to supported versions (e.g., `net6.0` or `net8.0` instead of `net5.0`/`netcoreapp3.1`).\n2. Replace the two MSTest package references with a single `MSTest` package (v3.x).\n\nWould you like me to update the project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bdb51ea4-2e78-4e2d-8f0e-b6b998739a1c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has dropped support for some older frameworks. Let me provide guidance.\n\nMSTest v3 key breaking changes regarding TFM support:\n- Minimum supported .NET Framework is .NET Framework 4.6.2 (net462 is fine)\n- .NET Core 3.1 and .NET 5.0 are no longer supported — MSTest v3 requires .NET 6.0+ for the .NET (Core) side\n- So `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` will be problematic\n\n\n- Additionally, MSTest v3 consolidates the testing packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package, which replaces the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages.","outputTokens":468,"requestId":"2400:303613:24711FB:270B479:6A03112F"},"id":"d6ec4d59-93d8-4309-aae9-63cc7284a5bd","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:38:34.341Z","parentId":"eb0e01af-86b4-4824-ab34-8e11ab0a8f7e"}
